Name: Coffin-Siris syndrome 1
Definition: A Coffin-Siris syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of ARID1B on chromosome 6q25.3.

Name: Coffin-Siris syndrome 2
Definition: A Coffin-Siris syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of ARID1A on chromosome 1p36.11.

Name: Coffin-Siris syndrome 3
Definition: A Coffin-Siris syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of SMARCB1 on chromosome 22q11.23.

Name: Coffin-Siris syndrome 4
Definition: A Coffin-Siris syndrome that has_material_basis_in an autosomal dominant mutation of SMARCA4 on chromosome 19p13.2.

Name: Coffin-Siris syndrome 6
Definition: An early infantile epileptic encephalopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the GABBR2 gene on chromosome 9q22.
